esult<(RoutingKey, u16, u8), TxtError>  // returns ([u8;16], port, version)\n\n// Coordinator API (reme-transport)\ncoordinator.add_http_target(HttpTarget)\ncoordinator.remove_http_target(&TargetId) -> bool\ncoordinator.replace_http_target(&TargetId, HttpTarget) -> bool\n\n// HTTP target construction\nHttpTargetConfig::ephemeral(url: impl Into<String>) -> HttpTargetConfig\nHttpTarget::new(config: HttpTargetConfig) -> Result<HttpTarget, TransportError>\n\n// Identity verification\nHttpTransport::verify_identity(&self, base_url: &str, candidates: &[PublicID]) -> Result<Option<PublicID>, TransportError>\n// NOTE: This is on HttpTransport, not on individual targets. You'll need to construct a temporary HttpTransport or use reqwest directly.\n// Actually, simpler approach: just make an HTTP request to {url}/api/v1/identity?challenge={b64} directly with reqwest.\n\n// TargetId construction\nTargetId::http(url: &str) -> TargetId\n```\n\n## Dependencies to add\n\nIn `apps/client/Cargo.toml`:\n- `reme-discovery = { workspace = true }` (if not already there)\n\n## Branch Setup\n\n```bash\ngit switch feat/lan-discovery\ngit switch -c feat/discovery-controller\n```\n\n## Important Design Decisions\n\n- Controller handles new-vs-updated distinction internally (repeated PeerDiscovered for same instance_name = update)\n- Identity verification uses existing `/api/v1/identity?challenge=` endpoint\n- Strangers (peers whose routing key doesn't match any contact) are ignored for now — policy hooks come in Unit 11\n- Max 256 tracked peers to prevent resource exhaustion\n- Use `TargetCapabilities::ephemeral_defaults()` for discovered targets (send only, no fetch, no quorum credit)\n\n## After Implementation\n\n1. Run `cargo test --workspace` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` and `cargo fmt --all -- --check`\n2. Invoke the `simplify` skill to review and clean up your changes\n3. Commit with a clear message\n4. Push and create a PR with `gh pr create --base fea